column1: A note on the TYR states that the previous returns by this observer were unreliable and these are no better. Apparently he was in the habit of including water held in the rim of the gauge (up until the end of April 1877)
A wavy line has been drawn across the totals on the 1860s sheet.
1883 has six sets of duplicate values, five of which correspond with the same observer's other gauge.
There are a five duplicate values which match those of another observer's nearby gauge.
